01:09:55.931 --> 01:09:59.722
which was such
a beautiful thing.


1372
01:09:59.722 --> 01:10:04.056
Before that,
I'm not sure I knew
what a personal life was.


1373
01:10:04.056 --> 01:10:06.889
I thought life began

1374
01:10:06.889 --> 01:10:10.388
with, you know,
"Action!"


1375
01:10:10.388 --> 01:10:11.555
And then, "Cut!"

1376
01:10:13.513 --> 01:10:15.305
After my mom and dad
broke up,


1377
01:10:15.305 --> 01:10:17.513
I always thought
that I would do my best


1378
01:10:17.513 --> 01:10:19.680
that if I ever decided
someday to get married,


1379
01:10:19.680 --> 01:10:21.181
I wouldn't get divorced.

1380
01:10:21.181 --> 01:10:22.722
And then,
of course, I did.


1381
01:10:22.722 --> 01:10:24.931
( music playing )

1382
01:10:27.931 --> 01:10:31.347
Divorce in any situation
is painful.


1383
01:10:31.347 --> 01:10:34.305
And it's especially
painful for me


1384
01:10:34.305 --> 01:10:37.722
because I am a child
of divorce


1385
01:10:37.722 --> 01:10:39.388
and I know
what it felt like.


1386
01:10:39.388 --> 01:10:42.597
And so, you know,
I felt terrible for Max,


1387
01:10:42.597 --> 01:10:45.139
that he had
to endure that.


1388
01:10:48.597 --> 01:10:50.513
- ( music playing )
- ( people shouting )


1389
01:10:50.513 --> 01:10:54.097
- Jamie: My plane.
- Jamie! Jamie!


1390
01:10:57.931 --> 01:10:59.097
Mom?

1391
01:11:01.222 --> 01:11:03.097
- Mom?
- Frank Marshall:
"Empire of the Sun"


1392
01:11:03.097 --> 01:11:05.764
was about this young boy
growing up in Shanghai


1393
01:11:05.764 --> 01:11:07.764
who gets separated
from his parents


1394
01:11:07.764 --> 01:11:09.931
during
the Japanese invasion.


1395
01:11:09.931 --> 01:11:11.513
Mommy!

1396
01:11:11.513 --> 01:11:13.680
- Jamie!
- Mommy!


1397
01:11:13.680 --> 01:11:16.972
And he goes through
a tremendous transformation


1398
01:11:16.972 --> 01:11:20.430
and growing-up process.

1399
01:11:20.430 --> 01:11:22.931
Spielberg:
It was playing on
what I knew were my strengths,


1400
01:11:22.931 --> 01:11:26.513
being able
to take the dark,
grim reality of war


1401
01:11:26.513 --> 01:11:28.680
and put it
with a child's approach


1402
01:11:28.680 --> 01:11:31.931
in the way
this particular special child
saw that war.


1403
01:11:31.931 --> 01:11:34.181
( crowd clamoring )

1404
01:11:40.347 --> 01:11:42.056
Spielberg:
It was based
on the experiences


1405
01:11:42.056 --> 01:11:43.430
that J.G. Ballard had

1406
01:11:43.430 --> 01:11:45.972
in a Japanese
internment camp.


1407
01:11:49.139 --> 01:11:51.972
Jim was a lost boy
trying to figure out


1408
01:11:51.972 --> 01:11:53.972
where he belongs
in this world.


1409
01:11:56.139 --> 01:11:58.555
It's a movie about
growing up too quickly


1410
01:11:58.555 --> 01:12:01.388
and abandoning everything
that you once used


1411
01:12:01.388 --> 01:12:03.014
to keep yourself safe.

1412
01:12:06.680 --> 01:12:09.430
When you have nothing
to keep yourself safe,


1413
01:12:09.430 --> 01:12:11.513
you become a survivor
like all the rest,


1414
01:12:11.513 --> 01:12:13.388
and you grow up
awfully quickly.


1415
01:12:15.056 --> 01:12:16.764
Christian Bale:
It's an extraordinary story


1416
01:12:16.764 --> 01:12:19.181
of the resilience
of children,


1417
01:12:19.181 --> 01:12:21.222
this incredible survivor

1418
01:12:21.222 --> 01:12:23.931
who manages to have
more fortitude to him


1419
01:12:23.931 --> 01:12:27.889
than, really,
any of the adults
around him.


1420
01:12:32.931 --> 01:12:36.805
Scorsese:
It's in the great tradition
of epic filmmaking.


1421
01:12:36.805 --> 01:12:40.472
That sports stadium
at the end when all the goods,


1422
01:12:40.472 --> 01:12:42.680
all the stuff
that had been stolen
is there,


1423
01:12:42.680 --> 01:12:45.388
the surrealism of that

1424
01:12:45.388 --> 01:12:50.388
and what it makes you feel
at that time and place,


1425
01:12:50.388 --> 01:12:51.764
the sense of what
the world was like,


1426
01:12:51.764 --> 01:12:55.263
how it had fallen apart,
all of civilization.


1427
01:12:55.263 --> 01:12:57.513
( music playing )

1428
01:13:11.805 --> 01:13:16.347
Scorsese:
And then, something even
more disturbingly beautiful,


1429
01:13:16.347 --> 01:13:19.430
and that is the glow
from the atom bomb.


1430
01:13:24.305 --> 01:13:27.764
It's like
a soul transcending
into another life.


1431
01:13:29.181 --> 01:13:31.847
Mrs. Victor.

1432
01:13:31.847 --> 01:13:37.305
This is very poetic
and... mystical.


1433
01:13:40.347 --> 01:13:43.764
- ( man speaks Japanese )
