1434
01:13:47.764 --> 01:13:49.430
Stoppard:
This was war


1435
01:13:49.430 --> 01:13:53.680
and it was death
and real horror.


1436
01:13:53.680 --> 01:13:56.097
And it was like
an end of innocence


1437
01:13:56.097 --> 01:13:58.430
for the Spielberg child.

1438
01:13:58.430 --> 01:14:00.722
( children's choir
singing in Welsh )


1439
01:14:00.722 --> 01:14:03.263
Stoppard:
I think it was
a truly great film,


1440
01:14:03.263 --> 01:14:05.597
but, for me,
it ultimately shaded


1441
01:14:05.597 --> 01:14:10.847
into an unnecessary softness
or sentimentality.


1442
01:14:10.847 --> 01:14:12.722
I don't know
where it comes from,


1443
01:14:12.722 --> 01:14:15.722
but he likes
and enjoys sentiment.


1444
01:14:15.722 --> 01:14:17.139
It's part of him.

1445
01:14:26.764 --> 01:14:29.305
Scott:
At the time, he was not
dismissed, exactly,


1446
01:14:29.305 --> 01:14:31.931
by a lot of critics,
but sort of looked at
a little skeptically.


1447
01:14:31.931 --> 01:14:33.305
"Oh, he wants
to be serious now.


1448
01:14:33.305 --> 01:14:34.972
Oh, he's trying to make
serious movies.


1449
01:14:34.972 --> 01:14:37.263
Oh, now he wants it"--
