1451
01:14:40.847 --> 01:14:42.472
to say about any artist.

1452
01:14:42.472 --> 01:14:44.889
Kennedy:
It definitely hurt
his feelings.


1453
01:14:44.889 --> 01:14:46.513
I don't think anybody
as an artist


1454
01:14:46.513 --> 01:14:49.139
wants to feel like
they're being pigeonholed


1455
01:14:49.139 --> 01:14:53.014
in a way that other people
are determining who they are.


1456
01:14:53.014 --> 01:14:55.430
And when Steven
began to explore


1457
01:14:55.430 --> 01:14:57.889
other kinds
of more serious stories,


1458
01:14:57.889 --> 01:15:00.764
they were very reluctant
to let him do that.


1459
01:15:00.764 --> 01:15:03.305
That was like,
"How dare you,
Steven Spielberg?


1460
01:15:03.305 --> 01:15:05.847
We've determined that you make
these kind of movies,


1461
01:15:05.847 --> 01:15:08.889
so why are you suddenly
trying to make this?"


1462
01:15:08.889 --> 01:15:11.056
He doesn't
over-intellectualize,


1463
01:15:11.056 --> 01:15:15.181
but maybe as a filmmaker,
Steven was using those movies


1464
01:15:15.181 --> 01:15:17.722
as stepping stones
along the way.


1465
01:15:17.722 --> 01:15:20.263
He didn't know
where he was headed,


1466
01:15:20.263 --> 01:15:23.680
but I think he was exercising
those muscles, in a way,


1467
01:15:23.680 --> 01:15:26.472
to recognize
he could go there,


1468
01:15:26.472 --> 01:15:28.472
that it was okay.

1469
01:15:31.014 --> 01:15:33.263
( man singing
in Hebrew )


1470
01:15:41.056 --> 01:15:43.931
Spielberg:
My very first memory--
I was in a stroller.


1471
01:15:43.931 --> 01:15:45.639
I just remember
being wheeled somewhere,


1472
01:15:45.639 --> 01:15:49.139
and my grandmother
and grandfather were with me.


1473
01:15:49.139 --> 01:15:51.722
( singing continues )

1474
01:15:51.722 --> 01:15:55.222
We went into
this underground space.


1475
01:15:55.222 --> 01:15:58.764
There was a red light
over a set of doors.


1476
01:16:01.764 --> 01:16:03.639
And I just remember
getting closer and closer


1477
01:16:03.639 --> 01:16:06.347
to this red light
where all these old men--


1478
01:16:06.347 --> 01:16:11.097
just men were all
chanting something.


1479
01:16:11.097 --> 01:16:14.139
And the red light
was the Eternal Light,
the Ner Tamid,


1480
01:16:14.139 --> 01:16:16.972
and that's
my very first memory.


1481
01:16:19.805 --> 01:16:23.014
- Lacy: Do you believe
in God?
- Yes.


1482
01:16:23.014 --> 01:16:25.097
Tell me about that.
Where where does...?


1483
01:16:25.097 --> 01:16:27.472
It comes from my--

1484
01:16:27.472 --> 01:16:31.139
you know, my spiritual--
not even spiritual,


1485
01:16:31.139 --> 01:16:34.056
my religious roots
and family.


1486
01:16:37.305 --> 01:16:41.014
All my grandparents had
a very strong influence
over me.


1487
01:16:41.014 --> 01:16:43.388
My grandfather, Fievel,
played guitar


1488
01:16:43.388 --> 01:16:45.680
and he sang
all Yiddish Russian songs.


1489
01:16:45.680 --> 01:16:47.597
And my grandmother,
Jennie,


1490
01:16:47.597 --> 01:16:50.555
taught English to Hungarian
Holocaust survivors.


1491
01:16:54.931 --> 01:16:58.014
We were Orthodox.
I was raised Orthodox.


1492
01:16:58.014 --> 01:17:01.097
And tradition has been
a huge part of my family,


1493
01:17:01.097 --> 01:17:03.056
and religious studies,
and Hebrew school,


1494
01:17:03.056 --> 01:17:07.263
and bar mitzvahs,
and bat mitzvahs
for my sisters.


1495
01:17:07.263 --> 01:17:10.305
But we always
lived in neighborhoods
where there were no Jews.


1496
01:17:10.305 --> 01:17:14.014
And there was
a real cultural divide
in those days


1497
01:17:14.014 --> 01:17:16.263
between Jewish people
and Gentiles,


1498
01:17:16.263 --> 01:17:18.430
a real cultural divide.

1499
01:17:18.430 --> 01:17:20.056
Adler:
I remember
that at one point,


1500
01:17:20.056 --> 01:17:23.639
kids were standing outside
and chanting


1501
01:17:23.639 --> 01:17:26.056
"the Spielbergs
are dirty Jews."


1502
01:17:26.056 --> 01:17:29.347
Spielberg:
I certainly experienced
being excluded


1503
01:17:29.347 --> 01:17:32.472
and being picked on
and discriminated against.


1504
01:17:32.472 --> 01:17:34.305
All I wanted to do
was fit in.


1505
01:17:34.305 --> 01:17:37.972
And by being Jewish,
there was no way I could
fit into anything.


1506
01:17:37.972 --> 01:17:40.639
My grandfather
would come over
to spend a week with us,


1507
01:17:40.639 --> 01:17:43.347
and I'd be playing
in the front yard
seven houses down,


1508
01:17:43.347 --> 01:17:45.181
and my grandfather
would stand on our front porch


1509
01:17:45.181 --> 01:17:47.388
and yell my Hebrew name,
"Shmuel!"


1510
01:17:47.388 --> 01:17:49.430
As loud
as he could, "Shmuel!"


1511
01:17:49.430 --> 01:17:53.555
And all my friends would say,
"Is he talking to you?
That's your house."


1512
01:17:53.555 --> 01:17:56.222
And I immediately denied
that that was me.


1513
01:17:56.222 --> 01:17:59.056
"No, he must be calling
somebody else."


1514
01:17:59.056 --> 01:18:00.889
"Is your name Shmuel?"

1515
01:18:00.889 --> 01:18:02.430
And all my friends
started laughing.


1516
01:18:02.430 --> 01:18:04.139
"Shmuel?
What's Shmuel?"


1517
01:18:04.139 --> 01:18:05.430
And meanwhile,
in the background,


1518
01:18:05.430 --> 01:18:07.222
you can hear
my grandfather yelling


1519
01:18:07.222 --> 01:18:09.555
with a Russian accent,
"Shmuel!"


1520
01:18:09.555 --> 01:18:11.430
Anne:
Steve did not
want to be Jewish.


1521
01:18:11.430 --> 01:18:13.472
He didn't want to be Jewish
because it made us


1522
01:18:13.472 --> 01:18:15.181
too different
from everybody.


1523
01:18:15.181 --> 01:18:17.931
And the "Father Knows Best"
family


1524
01:18:17.931 --> 01:18:20.139
is an assimilated family.

1525
01:18:20.139 --> 01:18:22.764
And I think
he really yearned for that.


1526
01:18:22.764 --> 01:18:27.555
I began to deny
my Jewishness,


1527
01:18:27.555 --> 01:18:29.680
you know, began to deny

1528
01:18:29.680 --> 01:18:32.388
everything that I had
accepted as a child


1529
01:18:32.388 --> 01:18:33.931
and was not
willing to accept


1530
01:18:33.931 --> 01:18:36.388
if it was going
to make me a pariah.


1531
01:18:36.388 --> 01:18:38.139
I was ashamed of myself.

1532
01:18:38.139 --> 01:18:41.347
I still feel ashamed
of myself


1533
01:18:41.347 --> 01:18:46.056
even remembering
that long stretch of my life


1534
01:18:46.056 --> 01:18:49.555
where I didn't want
to be Jewish anymore.


1535
01:18:53.555 --> 01:18:55.513
When I first met Kate,

1536
01:18:55.513 --> 01:18:57.889
something that only happens
in the movies


1537
01:18:57.889 --> 01:18:59.181
happened to me.

1538
01:18:59.181 --> 01:19:04.263
It's a terrible cliché,
but bells began ringing.


1539
01:19:04.263 --> 01:19:07.263
It was love at first sight.
It really was.


1540
01:19:07.263 --> 01:19:08.931
There was something
that was


1541
01:19:08.931 --> 01:19:11.513
so both self-assured
about Katie


1542
01:19:11.513 --> 01:19:13.847
and reassuring for me.

1543
01:19:13.847 --> 01:19:16.597
There was
a kind of in-syncness.


1544
01:19:16.597 --> 01:19:18.680
We could talk
about anything,


1545
01:19:18.680 --> 01:19:20.931
and I couldn't get her
off my mind.


1546
01:19:20.931 --> 01:19:23.222
( choir singing
in Hebrew )


1547
01:19:30.430 --> 01:19:33.472
Spielberg:
Kate came into my world,
in my life,


1548
01:19:33.472 --> 01:19:35.764
with a deep fascination
with the traditions


1549
01:19:35.764 --> 01:19:38.139
and the depth
of the history of Judaism.


1550
01:19:38.139 --> 01:19:40.764
And she really wanted
to marry me as a Jew.


1551
01:19:40.764 --> 01:19:44.014
So, she converted to Judaism
just before we got married.


1552
01:19:44.014 --> 01:19:46.472
Sue: She said
she always felt like
she was coming home.


1553
01:19:46.472 --> 01:19:48.972
She always felt this was
where she was meant to be.


1554
01:19:48.972 --> 01:19:51.680
And so, as she studied Judaism
and got into it,


1555
01:19:51.680 --> 01:19:54.847
it brought Steve back around
to appreciating it.


1556
01:19:54.847 --> 01:19:56.889
Parkes:
Kate brought
something to Steven


1557
01:19:56.889 --> 01:20:00.139
that I don't
think Steven believed
he could ever have.


1558
01:20:00.139 --> 01:20:03.931
She is so dedicated
to the idea of family


1559
01:20:03.931 --> 01:20:07.181
in its, you know,
purest essence


1560
01:20:07.181 --> 01:20:10.056
that not only
did it bring him,


1561
01:20:10.056 --> 01:20:12.805
I think, a happiness
