02:05:58.847 --> 02:06:00.889
What are we doing?

2486
02:06:00.889 --> 02:06:03.347
( speaking Arabic )

2487
02:06:04.847 --> 02:06:06.139
What do I do?

2488
02:06:06.139 --> 02:06:08.222
Do you know
why we're here?


2489
02:06:08.222 --> 02:06:10.764
( speaking Arabic )

2490
02:06:19.097 --> 02:06:22.014
Hoberman: In "Munich,"
Spielberg is trying
to come to terms


2491
02:06:22.014 --> 02:06:24.097
with the war
against terror.


2492
02:06:24.097 --> 02:06:28.555
And he doesn't know
where he is on it.


2493
02:06:28.555 --> 02:06:30.847
He's-- he supports it,

2494
02:06:30.847 --> 02:06:34.597
but he's also
disturbed by it.


2495
02:06:34.597 --> 02:06:36.639
And so,
that's an example


2496
02:06:36.639 --> 02:06:39.430
of a kind of thoughtfulness
that goes into his work.


2497
02:06:39.430 --> 02:06:43.263
I mean,
he's the Hollywood equivalent
of a public intellectual.


2498
02:06:52.430 --> 02:06:56.097
Bana:
I remember when we shot
the telephone bomb sequence.


2499
02:06:57.305 --> 02:06:59.097
In that one dolly shot,

2500
02:06:59.097 --> 02:07:02.347
you got a complete
sense of the geography
of the entire scene.


2501
02:07:04.639 --> 02:07:07.388
Spielberg:
It took three days
to shoot the scene.


2502
02:07:07.388 --> 02:07:10.430
Everything had to be
from points of view.


2503
02:07:10.430 --> 02:07:12.889
There was the point of view
of the guys in the car.


2504
02:07:12.889 --> 02:07:17.139
So now we wait
for the red light.


2505
02:07:17.139 --> 02:07:20.305
Spielberg:
There was the point of view
of the man in the phone booth


2506
02:07:20.305 --> 02:07:21.972
who was gonna dial
the number.


2507
02:07:21.972 --> 02:07:24.181
There was a point of view
of Avner.


2508
02:07:24.181 --> 02:07:27.305
It's a triangle
of shots.


2509
02:07:27.305 --> 02:07:29.680
Geography
is one of the most
important things to me,


2510
02:07:29.680 --> 02:07:31.972
so the audience
isn't thrown into chaos


2511
02:07:31.972 --> 02:07:33.764
trying to figure out
the story you're telling.


2512
02:07:33.764 --> 02:07:36.513
The audience needs to be
clearer than you.


2513
02:07:38.889 --> 02:07:40.805
- Is the truck
blocking the signal?
- No.


2514
02:07:40.805 --> 02:07:42.305
Will the remote
still work?


2515
02:07:42.305 --> 02:07:43.972
Spielberg:
I can create suspense


2516
02:07:43.972 --> 02:07:47.347
if the audience knows
where all the players are,


2517
02:07:47.347 --> 02:07:48.931
and they know
what the stakes are,


2518
02:07:48.931 --> 02:07:51.222
and they know
that there's a ticking clock.


